    <stitle>HYDRO-MAX II BRAKE MONITOR SYSTEM - SWITCH ADJUSTMENT - 2042091C91</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="0">
        <title>2042091C91</title>
        <para>To adjust the 2042091C91 Hall effect switch, back off the lock nut and screw the switch in or out as
            required to achieve the proper air gap. The proper air gap dimension between the end of the switch and the
            magnet is .100 inch to .200 inch. With the key OFF, the brake booster pump must come on with light foot
            pressure. Re-adjust if necessary. Refer to TSI-96-08-04.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
